üî¨This is a nightly-only experimental API. (`ptr_to_from_bits`¬†[#91126](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/91126))

Casts a pointer to its raw bits.

This is equivalent to `as usize`, but is more specific to enhance readability. The inverse method is [`from_bits`](about:blank/primitive.pointer.html#method.from_bits-1 "primitive pointer").

In particular, `*p as usize` and `p as usize` will both compile for pointers to numeric types but do very different things, so using this helps emphasize that reading the bits was intentional.

##### [¬ß](#examples-27)Examples

```
#![feature(ptr_to_from_bits)]
let mut array = [13, 42];
let mut it = array.iter_mut();
let p0: *mut i32 = it.next().unwrap();
assert_eq!(<*mut _>::from_bits(p0.to_bits()), p0);
let p1: *mut i32 = it.next().unwrap();
assert_eq!(p1.to_bits() - p0.to_bits(), 4);
}
```

