##### [¬ß](#at-compiletime-3)At compiletime

**Note: Alignment at compiletime is experimental and subject to change. See the [tracking issue](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/104203) for details.**

At compiletime, the compiler may not know where a value will end up in memory. Calling this function on a pointer created from a reference at compiletime will only return `true` if the pointer is guaranteed to be aligned. This means that the pointer cannot be stricter aligned than the reference‚Äôs underlying allocation.

```
